                              GUEST EDITORIAL
     =================================================================


     Who Decides - Douglas Myers

                                 Who Decides?
                             D. Myers, 1:270/720

     One of the consequences of being an internationally-known Fidonet
     Busybody is that I am occasionally confused with someone with
     actual influence.  Such was the case recently when Catalin Bradu of
     Romania, the RC of Region 53 sent me information he really wanted to
     get to Bob Satti.

     He was under the mistaken impression that I would have the email
     address of Fido's Top Cop.  All I have is a calling plan which lets
     me call in the US and Canada for a dime a minute, so crashing
     netmail is almost trivial.  If I'd been smart, I'd have just sent it
     along and let it go.

     It was stuff I didn't want to hear about.  He was excommunicating
     someone named Gabi Andrei for Excessively Annoying Behavior in
     proselytizing his particular brand of religion.  Though he
     apparently had the support of his region, his ZC, Ward Dossche
     ordered him to reverse his ruling.  A few days later, Ward removed
     him as RC, placing someone in charge who didn't support the EAB
     action.

     Now who wants to get involved in this?  Who wants to support someone
     proselytizing in netmail and echomail?  But then, who wants to
     support the nasty business of excommunication?  Especially in
     far-off Romania?

     Who should be making these decisions anyway?  Should Excessively
     Annoying Behavior be determined by the folks in the region where it
     occurs, or is it the province of the Zone Coordinator?

     For that matter, who decides when a popularly-elected Regional
     Coordinator should be removed.  Is it the province of his
     electorate, or is it up to the Zone Coordinator?

