     ECHO TALK - David E. Waters on the Real Problem

                 . -- -- -- -- -- ECHO TALK -- -- -- -- -- .
                 | Food for thought from Fido's echomail.  |
                 | Purloined without permission by D Myers |
                 ` -- -- -- -- -- --  -  -- -- -- -- -- -- '

     David E. Waters on The Real Problem:
     -------------------------------------------------------------------
     There is no depth in Fido. For instance, there is no school for
     future Sysops. When we all die, thats it it's over. Nobody is
     trained to take over any of the "Jobs" in Fido. How many know the
     politics of how to get mail from N.A. to Austraila? (Show of hands
     please.)

     Sysoping will very quickly become a lost art like "canning" (you
     know those jars our Grandmothers had full of stuff when we were
     kids). The unreleased version of Trade Wars is a prime example, it
     ties directly through a server and does not need a BBS to run.

     I know I am a "Johnny come lately" and most folks figure I do not
     whats going on and for the most part they are right. I am also a
     locksmith and there are no new people (Kids, teenagers & young
     adults) training behind us at least not enough to keep open all the
     shops that are out there now. Which means the fewer there are the
     resource gets more expensive (think about that the next you call 2-3
     locksmiths for an estimate, what if there was only 1?).

     I'm 52 and no I do not know how old anybody else is and it really
     does not matter, we ALL die sometime. All of us better figure out
     how to solve this part first or the who is doing what will not
     matter if there is no what to do, because the mail and files will
     have stopped because somebody died and nobody could take thier
     place.

